Azure PowerShell is a module that allows users to manage Azure resources using PowerShell commands (cmdlets). It is widely used by system administrators and Windows users for automation and scripting.

PowerShell integrates deeply with Azure and provides structured commands that are easy to read and use. For example, creating a resource group or virtual machine can be done using simple cmdlets.

A real-life use case is enterprise automation. For instance, an IT administrator can write a PowerShell script to automatically provision user environments, assign roles, and configure resources when a new employee joins.

Another example is backup automation. PowerShell scripts can be scheduled to regularly back up data from Azure Storage or databases, ensuring business continuity.

PowerShell is particularly powerful in Windows environments where administrators are already familiar with scripting and system management tasks.
